    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# News Article Summarizer\\n\",\"**NLP Project 42 of 100**\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Project Overview\\n\",\"Summarize news articles into concise, neutral summaries using extractive (frequency-based) and abstractive (transformer-based) methods.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\"1. Implement extractive summarization with sentence scoring.\\n\",\"2. Use Hugging Face BART/T5 for abstractive summarization.\\n\",\"3. Evaluate with ROUGE metrics.\\n\",\"4. Compare extractive vs abstractive quality.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Problem Statement\\n\",\"Given a full news article, produce a shorter summary that captures the key facts.\\n\",\"\\n\",\"## Why This Matters\\n\",\"- News readers want quick summaries.\\n\",\"- Newsrooms use auto-summarization for alerts and digests.\\n\",\"- Summarization is a core NLP task with broad applications.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Dataset: CNN/DailyMail sample from Hugging Face.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\nfor pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\",\\\"numpy\\\",\\\"matplotlib\\\",\\\"seaborn\\\",\\\"datasets\\\",\\\"transformers\\\",\\\"rouge-score\\\"]:\\n    try: importlib.import_module(pkg.replace('-','_'))\\n    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\nprint('Ready.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, re\\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nSEED = 42; np.random.seed(SEED)\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Load Dataset\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"from datasets import load_dataset\\nds = load_dataset('cnn_dailymail', '3.0.0', split='test').shuffle(seed=SEED).select(range(50))\\ndf = ds.to_pandas()[['article','highlights']]\\ndf.columns = ['article','reference_summary']\\nprint(f'Loaded {len(df)} articles')\\nprint(f'Avg article length: {df[\\\"article\\\"].str.len().mean():.0f} chars')\\nprint(f'Avg summary length: {df[\\\"reference_summary\\\"].str.len().mean():.0f} chars')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Extractive Summarization (Frequency-Based)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"def extractive_summarize(text, n_sentences=3):\\n    sentences = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])\\\\s+', text)\\n    if len(sentences) <= n_sentences:\\n        return text\\n    # Score sentences by word frequency\\n    word_freq = {}\\n    for sent in sentences:\\n        for word in re.findall(r'\\\\w+', sent.lower()):\\n            word_freq[word] = word_freq.get(word, 0) + 1\\n    scores = []\\n    for sent in sentences:\\n        score = sum(word_freq.get(w, 0) for w in re.findall(r'\\\\w+', sent.lower()))\\n        scores.append(score)\\n    top_indices = sorted(range(len(scores)), key=lambda i: -scores[i])[:n_sentences]\\n    top_indices.sort()  # Keep original order\\n    return ' '.join(sentences[i] for i in top_indices)\\n\\ndf['extractive_summary'] = df['article'].apply(extractive_summarize)\\nprint('Example extractive summary:')\\nprint(df['extractive_summary'].iloc[0][:300])\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Abstractive Summarization (BART)\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"from transformers import pipeline\\nimport torch\\n\\ndevice = 0 if torch.cuda.is_available() else -1\\nsummarizer = pipeline('summarization', model='facebook/bart-large-cnn', device=device)\\n\\ndef abstractive_summarize(text, max_length=130, min_length=30):\\n    try:\\n        result = summarizer(text[:1024], max_length=max_length, min_length=min_length, do_sample=False)\\n        return result[0]['summary_text']\\n    except Exception as e:\\n        return f'Error: {e}'\\n\\n# Summarize first 10 articles (BART is slow)\\ndf_eval = df.head(10).copy()\\ndf_eval['abstractive_summary'] = df_eval['article'].apply(abstractive_summarize)\\nprint('Example abstractive summary:')\\nprint(df_eval['abstractive_summary'].iloc[0][:300])\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Evaluation with ROUGE\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"from rouge_score import rouge_scorer\\n\\nscorer = rouge_scorer.RougeScorer(['rouge1','rouge2','rougeL'], use_stemmer=True)\\n\\ndef compute_rouge(predictions, references):\\n    scores = {'rouge1':[], 'rouge2':[], 'rougeL':[]}\\n    for pred, ref in zip(predictions, references):\\n        s = scorer.score(ref, pred)\\n        for k in scores: scores[k].append(s[k].fmeasure)\\n    return {k: np.mean(v) for k, v in scores.items()}\\n\\next_rouge = compute_rouge(df_eval['extractive_summary'], df_eval['reference_summary'])\\nabs_rouge = compute_rouge(df_eval['abstractive_summary'], df_eval['reference_summary'])\\n\\nprint(f'{\\\"Method\\\":<25} {\\\"ROUGE-1\\\":>10} {\\\"ROUGE-2\\\":>10} {\\\"ROUGE-L\\\":>10}')\\nprint('-'*55)\\nprint(f'{\\\"Extractive\\\":<25} {ext_rouge[\\\"rouge1\\\"]:>10.4f} {ext_rouge[\\\"rouge2\\\"]:>10.4f} {ext_rouge[\\\"rougeL\\\"]:>10.4f}')\\nprint(f'{\\\"BART Abstractive\\\":<25} {abs_rouge[\\\"rouge1\\\"]:>10.4f} {abs_rouge[\\\"rouge2\\\"]:>10.4f} {abs_rouge[\\\"rougeL\\\"]:>10.4f}')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"metrics = pd.DataFrame({'Extractive': ext_rouge, 'BART': abs_rouge})\\nmetrics.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(8,4), edgecolor='black')\\nplt.title('ROUGE Scores: Extractive vs Abstractive'); plt.ylabel('Score')\\nplt.xticks(rotation=0); plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **BART abstractive summaries are more fluent and concise** than extractive.\\n\",\"- **Extractive is faster** and doesn't require GPU.\\n\",\"- **ROUGE captures overlap** but doesn't fully measure summary quality.\\n\",\"- **For production, combine both**: extractive for speed, abstractive for quality.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
